          Women's hormonal systems are intricate and dynamic, involving complex interactions between the hypothalamus, pituitary gland, ovaries, adrenals, and thyroid. Throughout a woman's life, hormonal fluctuations occur naturally due to menstrual cycles, pregnancy, perimenopause, and menopause.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
